title: Kenai Fjords National Park: Marine Mammals
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Marine Mammals                 Marine Mammals       Kenai Fjords National Park was established in part... "to protect seals, sea lions, other marine mammals, and marine and other birds and to maintain their hauling and breeding areas in their natural state, free of human activity which is disruptive to their natural processes." - Alaska National Interests Lands Conservation Act, 1980.    Â    The following marine mammals can be found in the waters around Kenai Fjords National Park.  sea otter  Dall's porpoise harbor porpoise Steller sea lion harbor seal orca (killer whale) fin whale gray whale humpback whale minke whale sei whale Pacific white-sided dolphin
